cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.RO, cs.IT 

The paper deals with the security of wireless transmissions in a vehicular cyber-physical system, which involves cryptography and network security. Therefore, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) are the most likely categories. The paper also involves control and coordination of autonomous vehicles, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper proposes a scheme for generating secret keys based on channel quantization, which involves information theory and optimization, and hence cs.IT (Information Theory) is also a likely category.
